- The `collectLeaves'` of the current tree is the concatenation of `collectLeaves'` of its children. So `dt.collectLeaves'.length = sum_{c in children} c.collectLeaves'.length`.
- By the induction hypothesis, these sums are equal.

But this is only true if the inductive construction of `DerivationTree` is as we supposed (i.e., if the `collectLeaves'` of the parent is the concatenation of the `collectLeaves'` of the children, which is not generally correct unless the `collectLeaves'` function is defined appropriately).

